thread.title: Big plays made difference for Sooners in 2014
thread.title_full: Big plays made difference for Sooners in 2014 | Dallas Morning News

author: Kate Hairopoulos
title: Big plays made difference for Sooners in 2014
text:
Texas outgained OU, 482 to 232 yards, in last season's 31-26 win for the Sooners. OU made up for the difference, in part, with a 91-yard kickoff return by Alex Ross and a 43-yard interception return for a touchdown by cornerback Zack Sanchez.
"To have a special play like that, and do something that might go down in that rivalry's history is pretty cool for me to have my foot in there," said Sanchez (Keller Central). "Obviously I try to make a play against these guys every year, as well as every other team. But it makes it more special that it was against Texas."
